instead /ɪnˈstɛd/

1. PHRASE If you do one thing instead of another, you do the first thing and not the second thing, as the result of a choice or a change of behaviour. 而不是… 

例： They raised prices and cut production, instead of cutting costs. 他们提高了价格，减少了产量，而没有削减成本。 

2. ADV If you do not do something, but do something else instead , you do the second thing and not the first thing, as the result of a choice or a change of behaviour. 而 [ADV with cl] 

例： My husband asked why I couldn't just forget about dieting and eat normally instead. 丈夫问我为什么就不能忘掉节食而正常吃饭。

</div>

